.TH "BREW\-GENERATE\-TAP\-MAN\-COMPLETIONS" "1" "April 2026" "Homebrew"
.SH NAME
brew\-generate\-tap\-man\-completions \- Generate shell completions and man pages for a tap\'s commands
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
\fBbrew\fP \fBgenerate\-tap\-man\-completions\fP [\fB\-\-tap=\fP\fItap\fP] [\fB\-\-no\-exit\-code\fP] [\fB\-\-open\-pr\fP] [\fB\-\-no\-pull\-requests\fP] [\fB\-\-no\-fork\fP]
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Generate shell completions and man pages for a tap\[u2019]s commands\.
.P
Reads each \fB*\.rb\fP file in \fBcmd/\fP and \fBdev\-cmd/\fP and writes Bash, ZSH, and Fish completion files into \fBcompletions/\fP, and Ronn man page sources (\fB\&\.1\.md\fP) and compiled roff (\fB\&\.1\fP) into \fBmanpages/\fP\&\. Stale files for removed commands are cleaned up automatically\. The tap is auto\-detected from the location of this command file\. Use \fB\-\-tap\fP to override\.
.P
Exits non\-zero when no files change (like \fBgit diff \-\-exit\-code\fP)\. This is the same convention used by Homebrew\[u2019]s \fBgenerate\-man\-completions\fP\&\. Pass \fB\-\-no\-exit\-code\fP to always exit 0\.
.P
Pass \fB\-\-verbose\fP for a summary of what was processed (commands found, files written/skipped, stale files removed)\. Pass \fB\-\-debug\fP for detailed diagnostics about tap resolution, command discovery, and per\-file write decisions\.
.SH "OPTIONS"
.TP
\fB\-d\fP, \fB\-\-debug\fP
Display any debugging information\.
.TP
\fB\-q\fP, \fB\-\-quiet\fP
Make some output more quiet\.
.TP
\fB\-v\fP, \fB\-\-verbose\fP
Make some output more verbose\.
.TP
\fB\-h\fP, \fB\-\-help\fP
Show this message\.
.TP
\fB\-\-tap\fP
Generate completions for \fItap\fP (default: auto\-detected from command location)\.
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-exit\-code\fP
Exit with code 0 even if no changes were made\.
.TP
\fB\-\-open\-pr\fP
Check for duplicate pull requests before allowing a PR to be opened\.
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-pull\-requests\fP
Do not check for duplicate pull requests\.
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-fork\fP
Don\[u2019]t try to fork the repository\.
